org.factcenter.qilin.primitives

Interface Cipher


  • public interface Cipher
    This interface represents generic public-key encryption (or commitment). It is actually only a namespace; the methods are defined in the Cipher.PK and Cipher.SK sub-interfaces.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      static interface  Cipher.PK<C,P,R>
      Represents the public key of a cipher.
      static interface  Cipher.SK<C,P,R>
      Represents the secret key of a cipher.
